d early modern portrayals of the body and mind and explicate the role they play in forging an intimate rapport.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEmpathy in literature. 0aEnglish literatureyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish literatureyMiddle English, 1100-1500xHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 4aChaucer, Geoffrey. 4aEmpathie. 4aPhänomenologie. 4aShakespeare, William. 4aVoluntarismus. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Emotions.2bisacsh  aChaucer.  aEmpathy.  aPhenomenology.  aShakespeare.  aVoluntarism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97815015154770 cprintz978150152252940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151546040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501515460423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501515460/original  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022